Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.93,0:11:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m going to marry Kurosu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.01,0:11:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosu? You?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.39,0:11:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He’s a really lonely person.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.02,0:11:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell, can’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.06,0:11:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you’re his one and only rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.19,0:12:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.49,0:12:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, now you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.36,0:12:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has the apocalypse research made a little progress?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.37,0:12:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More than it has at your place, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.50,0:12:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.34,0:12:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That year, I become Kurosu’s wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.47,0:12:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I called Shu and the others over from Oshima,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.14,0:12:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the first Christmas we tried to spend as a family…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.89,0:12:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was that fateful day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.85,0:12:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,December 24th, 2029.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.48,0:12:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa’s late.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.69,0:12:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where’s Shu?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.32,0:12:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bathroom, Miss Haruka.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.11,0:12:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shu and I will be fine here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.24,0:12:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You go pick up Papa, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.00,0:12:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet he got caught up in his research and forgot about meeting us again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.17,0:12:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don’t mind, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.71,0:12:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.77,0:13:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Apocalypse Virus exteriorizes and materializes the hearts of the infected.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.94,0:13:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I’ve found a genetic code that may be able to interfere with that process.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.12,0:13:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I’ve named it the “Void Genome”.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.91,0:13:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unreasonableness of the seeds’ selection
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.46,0:13:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}was restored to reason with the Void Genome,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.59,0:13:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}by exteriorizing the obscure thing we call the “heart”.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.26,0:13:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Apocalypse is not divine providence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.47,0:13:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can control it with human intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.68,0:13:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peeking into the diaries of other people isn’t a nice hobby, Shuuichirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.89,0:13:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosu…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.06,0:14:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you actually {\i1}solved{\i0} it all?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.73,0:14:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.03,0:14:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mysteries of evolution and natural selection?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.91,0:14:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Daath is losing its patience.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’ll be silenced if you don’t do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.17,0:14:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll negotiate with them for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.75,0:14:23.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s work together on this, Kurosu.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.42,0:14:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No need.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.34,0:14:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know other places do things as a team, but I personally can’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.43,0:14:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doing it as a team would only dilute my thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.23,0:14:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t treat me like a fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.81,0:14:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.48,0:14:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m wasting my time letting too many cooks spoil the soup, is that what you’re saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.36,0:14:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that’s not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t drag my friend into the jam I’m in, can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.57,0:14:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t lie to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.37,0:14:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were jealous of my position,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.41,0:14:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you tried to get back at me by getting results
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.00,0:15:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while using deliberately inferior equipment!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.09,0:15:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.00,0:15:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would I be jealous of you for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.14,0:15:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.31,0:15:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I admit it, Kurosu.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.94,0:15:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.15,0:15:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you’ve made one big mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.57,0:15:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re no friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.34,0:15:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosu!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.96,0:15:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.69,0:16:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.57,0:16:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Void can temporarily house the Voids of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.07,0:16:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time, it can isolate and absorb cancer cells,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.66,0:16:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as the Apocalypse Virus’ genetic material itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.25,0:16:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s good. Souta must be cured, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.42,0:16:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Shu!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.13,0:16:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t use that power anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.05,0:16:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how hard you try to get Inori back,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.43,0:16:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it might be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.02,0:16:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The transplanting of Mana’s consciousness into Inori
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.23,0:16:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had already finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.44,0:16:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But to make her complete,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.19,0:16:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all the factors of hers that scatted during Lost Christmas…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.74,0:16:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The shards of her that had mixed with people’s Voids…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.24,0:17:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,…had to be collected.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.37,0:17:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s what you were being forced to do over the past few months.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.92,0:17:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.17,0:17:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she’s regained most of her power.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.59,0:17:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s why Gai’s been setting deadlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.34,0:17:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s just another reason why I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.64,0:17:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.23,0:17:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shu…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.53,0:17:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The helicopters are about to take off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.45,0:17:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I trust you’ll come with us, Shu?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.66,0:17:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Connect those cables!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.62,0:17:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The APU’s are hooked up! {OVERLAP THRU NEXT THREE LINES}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.95,0:17:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0001,,{\an8\pos(640,-5)}Fuel! Hey, where are the filters?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.45,0:17:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Container coming through! {OVERLAP ENDS HERE}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.79,0:17:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s almost time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.83,0:17:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.38,0:17:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really okay leaving things like this, Souta?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.76,0:17:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Ouma!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.55,0:18:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this everybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.06,0:18:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m giving you back your Voids.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.52,0:18:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shu?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.48,0:18:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! If you do that, your power will—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.15,0:18:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have to give them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.02,0:18:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I die while I’m still borrowing them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.44,0:18:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everyone else will die too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.07,0:18:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.15,0:18:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll take on the cancer and the virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.49,0:18:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You come here too, Ayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.49,0:18:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shu…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.13,0:18:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Screw that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.84,0:18:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, you didn’t have any objections about taking them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.01,0:18:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and now you’re giving them back?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.22,0:18:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you going to fight, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.47,0:18:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My arm’s not too weak to fire a gun with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.93,0:18:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.18,0:18:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you can win against Gai like that, Shu?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.43,0:18:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m going to use this power to save Inori and everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:18:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not to defeat Gai with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.94,0:18:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something wrong with that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.94,0:18:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to keep my Void.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.20,0:19:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you fail, our lives are forfeit anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.37,0:19:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s the gist of it. {LOL, THAT’S THE SIZE OF IT WHAT}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.91,0:19:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’re fine with that, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.16,0:19:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Souta?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.04,0:19:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.05,0:19:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.72,0:19:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not that I really get it…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.59,0:19:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it’s okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.43,0:19:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?! Cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.85,0:19:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m not trying to give your Void back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.81,0:19:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s shake hands, Souta.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.27,0:19:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to shake hands to make up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.40,0:19:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said so yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.86,0:19:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can’t part ways like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.66,0:19:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s what I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.93,0:20:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your hand…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m sorry, Shu…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.14,0:20:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.77,0:20:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so scared of you…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.06,0:20:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hated being like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.98,0:20:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.53,0:20:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Shu…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.91,0:20:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay my friend…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.29,0:20:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.66,0:20:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’re friends, Souta.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.75,0:20:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’ll be friends for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.89,0:20:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kurosu was the kind of person who could do anything by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.69,0:20:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.52,0:21:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And he was always alone because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.90,0:21:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But the truth was, he was really lonely…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.41,0:21:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He wanted to be with everyone else…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.12,0:21:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That’s why he named you “Shu”, which stands for “group”.
